        <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">No more than 5 functions per file</li>

Any use of functions like <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>printf</code>, <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>puts</code>, etc&hellip; is forbidden</li>

If you do it won&rsquo;t be taken into account</li>

            <h3 class="panel-title" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: inherit; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px;">0. strcat</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body" style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 15px;">
            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px;">Write a function that concatenates two strings.</p>
            <ul style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
                <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Prototype: <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>char *_strcat(char *dest, char *src);</code></li>
                <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">This function appends the <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>src</code> string to the <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>dest</code> string, overwriting the terminating null byte (<code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>\0</code>) at the end of <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>dest</code>, and then adds a terminating null byte</li>
                <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Returns a pointer to the resulting string <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>dest</code></li>
            </ul>
            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px;">FYI: The standard library provides a similar function: <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>strcat</code>. Run <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>man strcat</code> to learn more.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="panel-body" style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 15px;">
            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px;">Write a function that concatenates two strings.</p>
            <ul style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
                <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Prototype: <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>char *_strncat(char *dest, char *src, int n);</code></li>
                <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">The <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>_strncat</code> function is similar to the <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>_strcat</code> function, except that<ul style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;">
                        <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">it will use at most <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>n</code> bytes from <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>src</code>; and</li>
                        <li style="box-sizing: border-box;"><code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>src</code> does not need to be null-terminated if it contains <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>n</code> or more bytes</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Return a pointer to the resulting string <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>dest</code></li>
            </ul>
            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px;">FYI: The standard library provides a similar function: <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>strncat</code>. Run <code style='box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding: 2px 4px; color: rgb(199, 37, 78); background-color: rgb(249, 242, 244); border-radius: 4px;'>man strncat</code> to learn more.</p>

            <div style="box-sizing: border-box; display: flex;"><span class="label label-info" style="box-sizing: border-box; display: inline; padding: 0.2em 0.6em 0.3em; font-size: 10.5px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: center; white-space: nowrap; vertical-align: baseline; border-radius: 0.25em; background-color: rgb(152, 163, 174);">mandatory</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body" style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 15px;">
            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px;">Write a function that copies a string.</p>
